Vice President Mike Pence held a press conference at JLS Automation in Pennsylvania to discuss the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and the ongoing discussions with Mexico regarding illegal immigration. Pence emphasized the positive impact of the USMCA on the economy and urged Congress to pass it. He also addressed the recent announcement of potential tariffs on Mexican goods and stated that Mexico must do more to address the crisis of illegal immigration at the southern border. Pence mentioned that progress has been made in the discussions with Mexico, but emphasized that the tariffs will still be imposed on Monday unless significant action is taken. He expressed hope for a resolution and emphasized that President Trump's priority is to end the crisis at the border.